    <p>Knots have the advantage of being flexible: So long as you don’t tear the rope, you can move it around to minimize the distortion. Gromov asked a question about “torus knots,” which can be drawn on the surface of a doughnut without crossing themselves. You can think of the doughnut as a sort of mold that helps make the structure of the knots clear, as seen below:</p>
